	<text>
		<body>
			<pb n="1"/>
				<p><add>Hebrew</add></p>
				<p rend="align(right)"><hi rend="underline">Kalid.</hi></p>
				<p>With the help of God&#44; blessed be He</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">To the princes and officers of the cities of<lb/> <placeName>America</placeName>&#44; may God bless you&#44; etc.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">After extending our greeting to you&#44; I<lb/> want to let you know that some time ago<lb/> I announced ot all the lands that which I<lb/> have done in order that Jews might have a livelihood<lb/> from farming and manual labor in the <placeName>holy land</placeName>.<lb/>  For&#44; as our sages said&#44; &#34;All the artisans are <del>dest</del><lb/> destined to arise&#44; etc.&#34;&#44; As a result I have<lb/> had great heartache and financial loss&#44; and I<lb/> requested of you that you send us one gift&#42;.  Dur&#45;<lb/>ing the past year&#44; however&#44; all my mules died&#44;<lb/> and everything was almost lost.  For I did not have<lb/> enough capital to purchase mules and to work the<lb/> sail.  But God provided us with <del>a way of escape</del> deliverance<lb/> through the <persName>Signora Mrs. Monni Campanile</persName>&#44;<lb/> who lives here in the <placeName>holy land</placeName> and is engaged<lb/> in agriculture by employing Israelites who gain<lb/> a livelihood through her.  She also did me this<lb/> kindness and paid for everything from her own<lb/> pocket&#44; so as to enable me to work the soil at present.</p>
				<p>&#42; I cannot understand the nature<lb/> of this gift.  It is either a gift of a<lb/> tool <del> <add>&#63;</add> </del> or a sum of money.</p>
			<pb n="2"/>
				<p>Nevertheless&#44; money is still necessary to<lb/> complete all the buildings and other needed ex&#45;<lb/>penses.  And now I come with this request<lb/> that you have mercy upon us and upon our<lb/> land and our in&#45;<sic>heritance</sic>&#44; so that through<lb/> you and through her we might succeed&#44; and<lb/> many other families of our fellow&#45;Israelites should<lb/> gain a livelihood.  If you desire&#44; let us<lb/> know&#44; and we shall send you from the fruit of<lb/> the <placeName>holy land</placeName> ethrogim&#44; Kosher and beautiful&#44;<lb/>which are grown in our orchards&#44; and by the<lb/> hand of Israelites.  Thus will you be<lb/> privileged to utter your benedictions and to fulfill<lb/> your commandments with regard to the fruit of<lb/> the <placeName>holy land</placeName>.  We look forward to your reply<lb/> and I remain&#44; with a greeting of peace&#44; he<lb/> who prays for your good fortune forever.<lb/>  Signed in the <placeName>Holy Land</placeName>&#44; <placeName>Jaffa</placeName>&#44; <date>Adar&#44; 1854</date>.</p>
				<p><persName role="author">Raphael Judah</persName>&#44; Son of <persName>Menachem<lb/> Halevy</persName>&#44; community leader<lb/> in the <placeName>Holy Land</placeName></p>
